com.cyc.baseclient.connection

Class SublWorkerEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.EventObject
      • com.cyc.baseclient.connection.SublWorkerEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WorkerEvent, Serializable

    public class SublWorkerEvent
extends EventObject
implements WorkerEvent

    WorkerEvent is designed to represent the state of an event that can be generated by Workers and passed to the WorkerListener interface.

      • SublWorkerEvent

        public SublWorkerEvent(Worker source,
                       Object newData,
                       float percentComplete)
        Creates a new instance of WorkerEvent, this constructor is appropriate only for creating data available events.

      • SublWorkerEvent

                       WorkerStatus status,
                       Exception e)
        Creates a new instance of WorkerEvent, this constructor is appropriate only for creating termination events.
        Parameters:
        source - the Worker that generates the event
        status - why this Worker terminated
        e - exception thrown while doing work (or null if none thrown)
